CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 29, 1952, pg. 1 reads: "Happy Moments in Lives Of These "Favorite Churchwomen" - These five contestants shared honors last Thursday night in A. Leo Weil School Auditorium...In the insert, at the bottom, Mrs. Lucy Coleman, second prize winner, smiles becasue she won $75 for her church..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of four women, including Lucy Coleman, standing at podium, and Jessie Vann, standing on right, and two men, including P. L. Prattis seated on left, gathered on stage in A. Leo Weil school during "Favorite Churchwoman's" contest award program
